    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Advance
    Advance class is used to move some armies from one of the current player's territories (source) to an adjacent territory (target).
    AdvanceTest
     
    Airlift
    Airlift class is used to advance some armies from one of the current player’s territories to any another territory.
    AirliftTest
     
    Blockade
    Blockade class is used to triple the number of armies on one of the current player’s territories and make it a neutral territory.
    BlockadeTest
     
    Bomb
    Bomb class is used to destroy half of the armies located on an opponent’s territory that is adjacent to one of the current player’s territories.
    BombTest
     
    Card
    The special orders represented by cards.
    Continent
    Represents a Continent in the game
    Country
    Represents a Country in the game.
    Deploy
    Deploy class is used to place some armies on one of the current player’s territories.
    DeployTest
     
    Diplomacy
    Diplomacy class is used to prevent attacks between the current player and another player until the end of the turn.
    DiplomacyTest
     
    ExecuteOrder
     
    GameEngine
    GameEngine class that works as the controller for the game flow Manages the game stages and has the list for Player and Country objects: d_playerList: list of player objects d_countryList: list of country objects
    GameEngineTest
     
    GameplayTestSuite
     
    InputOutput
    InputOutput class manages all Input and Output operations that are used in Map Editor and Gameplay.
    IssueOrder
    Defines IssueOrder phase and its methods.
    LogEntryBuffer
    LogEntryBuffer class to store the log entries and notify the observers.
    LogFileWriter
     
    LogObserver
    LogObserver interface to update the log buffer.
    Main
    Main class to run the application
    MainTestSuite
     
    MapReader
    MapReader class to load and validate domination map files.
    MapsTestSuite
     
    Menu
    Defines Menu phase and its methods.
    Order
    Order class containing the orders information for its future identification inside the main.com.gameplay loop String d_countryName target country name to assign the order int d_numArmy number of reinforcements involved in the order String d_orderType type of the order being issued and executed Player d_player player owner of the order
    OrdersTestSuite
     
    Parsing
    Parsing class manages the parsing of user commands.
    ParsingTest
    CommandTest class provides testing for the arguments passed in the user commands.
    Phase
    Phase interface that defines the methods for the game phases
    Player
    Player class containing the Player related methods and information Queue of Order nature designated for the orders issued by a player Integer d_numReinforcement designated for the number of reinforcements a player possesses List of Country nature ownedCountries designated for countries a player possesses
    Postload
    Postload phase class.
    Preload
     
    Startup
    Defines Startup phase and its methods.
